meaning_str.bing:
n. 毕业生；大学毕业生；学士学位获得者
v. 大学毕业；获得学位（尤指学士）；毕业（尤指中学）
adj. 得学士称号的；刻度的
网络. 研究生；研究所；量筒

毕业生；大学毕业生；学士学位获得者
大学毕业；获得学位（尤指学士）；毕业（尤指中学）

大学毕业生；学位获得者；毕业证书持有者
毕业；获得学位；逐渐变化；逐步发展；按等级划分；划分等级；刻划刻度；做出标记；授予…学位；完成学业

1.en: I'd like to tell you about when I was a graduate student, and I spent one summer on the boat in the L studying marine life.
1.cn: 我想给你们讲我当研究生时的事，我在一艘船上呆了一个夏天享受我的海洋生活。

2.en: I explained as best I could that I had not been a professor but a graduate student, and part of my training was teaching undergraduates.
2.cn: 我尽可能地告诉他我不是教授，只是一名研究生，我接受的训练的一部分包括给本科生上课。

3.en: So by the time you graduate college, you think you've seen it all when it comes to rolls. Well think again.
3.cn: 等到毕业的时候，你一定觉得你已经尝尽各式各样的寿司拼盘。

0.en: You thought the opposite of "stupid loser" was "community college graduate"?
0.cn: 你觉得"很傻很衰"的反义词是"社区大学毕业生"？

1.en: Phil and I have prepared something very special for our brilliant graduate, Alex. Okay, you ready?
1.cn: 菲尔和我给我们聪明的毕业生艾丽克斯准备了一个特别的贺礼。你准备好了吗？

2.en: A 25-year-old Harvard Law graduate took South Carolina State Senate District Fourteen by storm. His name was Francis J. Underwood.
2.cn: 25岁的哈佛法学院毕业生席卷了南卡罗莱纳州州参议院第14区，他的名字是弗兰西斯·J·安德伍德。

3.en: I'm even prouder to share a fundamental truth that you might not have learned, even as graduate of Harvard, unless you studied the ancient Greek role with professor Nagy.
3.cn: 同时，我要更自豪地分享一件事，尽管你们是哈佛毕业生，可能也不知道这个，除非你攻读的是纳吉教授的古希腊角色。

4.en: Now, because I had been a football star and war hero and national celebrity and a shrimping boat captain and a college graduate, the city fathers of Greenbow, Alabama, decided to get together and offered me a fine job.
4.cn: 现在因为我成了足球明星和战争英雄，以及全国知名的人物和捕虾船的船长，以及大学毕业生，亚拉巴马州绿茵镇的父老乡亲，决定给我一个好工作。

5.en: Got myself a Mr. Sam Witwicky, recent college graduate.
5.cn: 来了一个山姆威特维奇先生，刚毕业。

6.en: So as you graduate today, I want to put some pressure on you.
6.cn: 在你们毕业的今天，我希望给你们一些压力。

7.en: Howard. I appreciate the gesture, but this is a graduate-level physics class.
7.cn: 霍华德，感谢你的提议，但这是研究生阶段的物理课程。

8.en: Graduate school should probably do a better job of screening those people out.
8.cn: 学校毕业后可以找个比大多数人做得都好的工作。

9.en: And I made my company promise that I can't be transferred again until you graduate.
9.cn: 我要我的公司答应在你毕业前我不会再调动了。

10.en: By receiving their badges, the following explorers will graduate to Senior Explorers.
10.cn: 现在颁发徽章，以下探险者将升级为高级探险者。

11.en: But if we're all going to die the moment we graduate, isn't it what we do before that counts?
11.cn: 但如果我们在毕业的那一刻死去，难道不是在毕业前经历的一切最重要吗?

12.en: Looking out at your fresh young faces, I remember when I too was deciding my academic future as a lowly graduate student.
12.cn: 看见你们朝气蓬勃的脸庞，我回想起了我决定步入学术道路的那一刻，那时我还是个卑微的研究生。

13.en: Robbie Feinberg, the pinhead, took five years to finish high school. Alden Kupferberg, the Sea Otter, didn't even graduate.
13.cn: Robbie Feinberg "没头脑"花了5年才读完了高中，Alden Kupferberg "海獭"连高中都没毕业。

14.en: As mayor of Zootopia, I am proud to announce that my mammal inclusion initiative, has produced its first police academy graduate.
14.cn: 作为动物城的市长，我很荣幸地宣布，哺乳动物选拔行动的第一批警校学员已经毕业了。

15.en: Only 211. Don't worry. In deference to you, I kept them all at a high school graduate reading level. Thanks, pal. You got it, buddy.
15.cn: 区区211个，别担心 为了照顾你，这份高中毕业就能读懂，还得谢你，哥们儿。客气啥...姐们儿。

16.en: A colleague of mine did her graduate thesis on the fungus that grows on improperly sterilized manicure implements. Well don't tell me that's not "girl talk".
16.cn: 我的一个同事的毕业论文就写的是消毒不当的美甲工具上滋生的霉菌，别说这不是女生话题。

17.en: At Harvard's commencement tomorrow as your dean described, each school is gonna stand up and graduate together, the college, the law school, the med school and so on.
17.cn: 你们院长也讲了，在明天的哈佛毕业典礼上，每个学院都要起立并一同毕业。本科部、法学院、医学院等等。
